@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms of Service";
}

<div class="page-header reveal">
    <div>
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">Last updated: June 21, 2026</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card reveal" style="max-width:850px; margin:0 auto; padding:2.5rem; line-height:1.8;">
    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--accent-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:2rem;">
        By accessing or using the JobBoard website, services, or communication applications, you agree to comply with and be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--accent-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">2. Account Creation & Integrity</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:1rem;">
        When creating an account, you must select the appropriate role:
    </p>
    <ul style="color:var(--text-secondary); padding-left:1.5rem; margin-bottom:2rem; list-style-type:disc;">
        <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;"><strong>Candidates</strong> are individuals looking for employment opportunities. They must provide accurate details and uploaded resumes.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;"><strong>Employers</strong> represent legally recognized business entities looking to recruit talent.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:2rem;">
        You are responsible for keeping your login credentials confidential. Any activity registered under your account is your sole responsibility.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--accent-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">3. Job Postings & Moderation</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Employers may post job openings. We reserve the right to review, edit, suspend, or delete any job listings that are fake, duplicate, misleading, or promote illegal activities. Administrators moderate listings to ensure a safe and professional community platform.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--accent-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">4. Applications & CV Uploads</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Candidates may apply to active job postings. When applying, you may upload a cover letter and a single CV file in PDF or DOCX format. The file must not exceed 1MB. Files containing malware, macro viruses, or offensive content will be deleted immediately, and user accounts may be suspended.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--accent-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">5. Chat Feature Code of Conduct</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Our messaging platform, including the real-time mini-chat drawer panel, is intended for recruiting discussions only. Users are strictly prohibited from using the chat for harassment, spam, advertising services, or sending unsolicited files. Unprofessional behavior will result in account termination.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--accent-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">6. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:2rem;">
        JobBoard is provided on an "as-is" and "as-available" basis. We do not guarantee the accuracy of job postings, the qualifications of candidates, or the success of any application process.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--accent-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">7. Contact Us</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);">
        If you have questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us at: <br/>
        ✉️ Email: legal@jobboard.com
    </p>
</div>
